Text: For a show that has very little action,the writers are quite good at keeping us watching.Although last week Will did shoot the intruder in the head and his friend did a cleanup job,this is the exception.Now Will sleeps with a baseball bat and his dead friends wife answers the door with a gigantic butcher knife.Lots of paranoia here.It goes to show you that a show about intelligence and written with intelligence can work.IMHO
I like LeCarre novels, I like that pace, it's excellent cast, written and directed in best fashion of British spy series.
